40void
41gf119_disp_vblank_init(struct nv50_disp *disp, int head)
42{
43 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
44 nvkm_mask(device, 0x6100c0 + (head * 0x800), 0x00000001, 0x00000001);
45}

47void
48gf119_disp_vblank_fini(struct nv50_disp *disp, int head)
49{
50 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
51 nvkm_mask(device, 0x6100c0 + (head * 0x800), 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
52}

54static struct nvkm_output *
55exec_lookup(struct nv50_disp *disp, int head, int or, u32 ctrl,
56 u32 *data, u8 *ver, u8 *hdr, u8 *cnt, u8 *len,
57 struct nvbios_outp *info)
58{
59 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
60 struct nvkm_bios *bios = subdev->device->bios;
61 struct nvkm_output *outp;
62 u16 mask, type;
63
64 if (or < 4) {
65 type = DCB_OUTPUT_ANALOG;
66 mask = 0;
67 } else {
68 or -= 4;
69 switch (ctrl & 0x00000f00) {
70 case 0x00000000: type = DCB_OUTPUT_LVDS; mask = 1; break;
71 case 0x00000100: type = DCB_OUTPUT_TMDS; mask = 1; break;
72 case 0x00000200: type = DCB_OUTPUT_TMDS; mask = 2; break;
73 case 0x00000500: type = DCB_OUTPUT_TMDS; mask = 3; break;
74 case 0x00000800: type = DCB_OUTPUT_DP; mask = 1; break;
75 case 0x00000900: type = DCB_OUTPUT_DP; mask = 2; break;
76 default:
77 nvkm_error(subdev, "unknown SOR mc %08x\n", ctrl);
78 return NULL;
79 }
80 }
81
82 mask = 0x00c0 & (mask << 6);
83 mask |= 0x0001 << or;
84 mask |= 0x0100 << head;
85
86 list_for_each_entry(outp, &disp->base.outp, head) {
87 if ((outp->info.hasht & 0xff) == type &&
88 (outp->info.hashm & mask) == mask) {
89 *data = nvbios_outp_match(bios, outp->info.hasht,
90 outp->info.hashm,
91 ver, hdr, cnt, len, info);
92 if (!*data)
93 return NULL;
94 return outp;
95 }
96 }
97
98 return NULL;
99}
100
101static struct nvkm_output *
102exec_script(struct nv50_disp *disp, int head, int id)
103{
104 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
105 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
106 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
107 struct nvkm_output *outp;
108 struct nvbios_outp info;
109 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len;
110 u32 data, ctrl = 0;
111 int or;
112
113 for (or = 0; !(ctrl & (1 << head)) && or < 8; or++) {
114 ctrl = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x640180 + (or * 0x20));
115 if (ctrl & (1 << head))
116 break;
117 }
118
119 if (or == 8)
120 return NULL;
121
122 outp = exec_lookup(disp, head, or, ctrl, &data, &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &info);
123 if (outp) {
124 struct nvbios_init init = {
125 .subdev = subdev,
126 .bios = bios,
127 .offset = info.script[id],
128 .outp = &outp->info,
129 .crtc = head,
130 .execute = 1,
131 };
132
133 nvbios_exec(&init);
134 }
135
136 return outp;
137}
138
139static struct nvkm_output *
140exec_clkcmp(struct nv50_disp *disp, int head, int id, u32 pclk, u32 *conf)
141{
142 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
143 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
144 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
145 struct nvkm_output *outp;
146 struct nvbios_outp info1;
147 struct nvbios_ocfg info2;
148 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len;
149 u32 data, ctrl = 0;
150 int or;
151
152 for (or = 0; !(ctrl & (1 << head)) && or < 8; or++) {
153 ctrl = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x660180 + (or * 0x20));
154 if (ctrl & (1 << head))
155 break;
156 }
157
158 if (or == 8)
159 return NULL;
160
161 outp = exec_lookup(disp, head, or, ctrl, &data, &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &info1);
162 if (!outp)
163 return NULL;
164
165 switch (outp->info.type) {
166 case DCB_OUTPUT_TMDS:
167 *conf = (ctrl & 0x00000f00) >> 8;
168 if (pclk >= 165000)
169 *conf |= 0x0100;
170 break;
171 case DCB_OUTPUT_LVDS:
172 *conf = disp->sor.lvdsconf;
173 break;
174 case DCB_OUTPUT_DP:
175 *conf = (ctrl & 0x00000f00) >> 8;
176 break;
177 case DCB_OUTPUT_ANALOG:
178 default:
179 *conf = 0x00ff;
180 break;
181 }
182
183 data = nvbios_ocfg_match(bios, data, *conf, &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &info2);
184 CTASSERT(__arraycount(info2.clkcmp) <= 0xff);
185 if (data && id < __arraycount(info2.clkcmp)) {
186 data = nvbios_oclk_match(bios, info2.clkcmp[id], pclk);
187 if (data) {
188 struct nvbios_init init = {
189 .subdev = subdev,
190 .bios = bios,
191 .offset = data,
192 .outp = &outp->info,
193 .crtc = head,
194 .execute = 1,
195 };
196
197 nvbios_exec(&init);
198 }
199 }
200
201 return outp;
202}

204static void
205gf119_disp_intr_unk1_0(struct nv50_disp *disp, int head)
206{
207 exec_script(disp, head, 1);
208}

210static void
211gf119_disp_intr_unk2_0(struct nv50_disp *disp, int head)
212{
213 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
214 struct nvkm_output *outp = exec_script(disp, head, 2);
215
216 /* see note in nv50_disp_intr_unk20_0() */
217 if (outp && outp->info.type == DCB_OUTPUT_DP) {
218 struct nvkm_output_dp *outpdp = nvkm_output_dp(outp);
219 struct nvbios_init init = {
220 .subdev = subdev,
221 .bios = subdev->device->bios,
222 .outp = &outp->info,
223 .crtc = head,
224 .offset = outpdp->info.script[4],
225 .execute = 1,
226 };
227
228 nvbios_exec(&init);
229 atomic_set(&outpdp->lt.done, 0);
230 }
231}

233static void
234gf119_disp_intr_unk2_1(struct nv50_disp *disp, int head)
235{
236 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
237 struct nvkm_devinit *devinit = device->devinit;
238 u32 pclk = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x660450 + (head * 0x300)) / 1000;
239 if (pclk)
240 nvkm_devinit_pll_set(devinit, PLL_VPLL0 + head, pclk);
241 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x612200 + (head * 0x800), 0x00000000);
242}

244static void
245gf119_disp_intr_unk2_2_tu(struct nv50_disp *disp, int head,
246 struct dcb_output *outp)
247{
248 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
249 const int or = ffs(outp->or) - 1;
250 const u32 ctrl = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x660200 + (or * 0x020));
251 const u32 conf = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x660404 + (head * 0x300));
252 const s32 vactive = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x660414 + (head * 0x300)) & 0xffff;
253 const s32 vblanke = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x66041c + (head * 0x300)) & 0xffff;
254 const s32 vblanks = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x660420 + (head * 0x300)) & 0xffff;
255 const u32 pclk = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x660450 + (head * 0x300)) / 1000;
256 const u32 link = ((ctrl & 0xf00) == 0x800) ? 0 : 1;
257 const u32 hoff = (head * 0x800);
258 const u32 soff = ( or * 0x800);
259 const u32 loff = (link * 0x080) + soff;
260 const u32 symbol = 100000;
261 const u32 TU = 64;
262 u32 dpctrl = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c10c + loff);
263 u32 clksor = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x612300 + soff);
264 u32 datarate, link_nr, link_bw, bits;
265 u64 ratio, value;
266
267 link_nr = hweight32(dpctrl & 0x000f0000);
268 link_bw = (clksor & 0x007c0000) >> 18;
269 link_bw *= 27000;
270
271 /* symbols/hblank - algorithm taken from comments in tegra driver */
272 value = vblanke + vactive - vblanks - 7;
273 value = value * link_bw;
274 do_div(value, pclk);
275 value = value - (3 * !!(dpctrl & 0x00004000)) - (12 / link_nr);
276 nvkm_mask(device, 0x616620 + hoff, 0x0000ffff, value);
277
278 /* symbols/vblank - algorithm taken from comments in tegra driver */
279 value = vblanks - vblanke - 25;
280 value = value * link_bw;
281 do_div(value, pclk);
282 value = value - ((36 / link_nr) + 3) - 1;
283 nvkm_mask(device, 0x616624 + hoff, 0x00ffffff, value);
284
285 /* watermark */
286 if ((conf & 0x3c0) == 0x180) bits = 30;
287 else if ((conf & 0x3c0) == 0x140) bits = 24;
288 else bits = 18;
289 datarate = (pclk * bits) / 8;
290
291 ratio = datarate;
292 ratio *= symbol;
293 do_div(ratio, link_nr * link_bw);
294
295 value = (symbol - ratio) * TU;
296 value *= ratio;
297 do_div(value, symbol);
298 do_div(value, symbol);
299
300 value += 5;
301 value |= 0x08000000;
302
303 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x616610 + hoff, value);
304}
305
306static void
307gf119_disp_intr_unk2_2(struct nv50_disp *disp, int head)
308{
309 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
310 struct nvkm_output *outp;
311 u32 pclk = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x660450 + (head * 0x300)) / 1000;
312 u32 conf, addr, data;
313
314 outp = exec_clkcmp(disp, head, 0xff, pclk, &conf);
315 if (!outp)
316 return;
317
318 /* see note in nv50_disp_intr_unk20_2() */
319 if (outp->info.type == DCB_OUTPUT_DP) {
320 u32 sync = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x660404 + (head * 0x300));
321 switch ((sync & 0x000003c0) >> 6) {
322 case 6: pclk = pclk * 30; break;
323 case 5: pclk = pclk * 24; break;
324 case 2:
325 default:
326 pclk = pclk * 18;
327 break;
328 }
329
330 if (nvkm_output_dp_train(outp, pclk, true))
331 OUTP_ERR(outp, "link not trained before attach");
332 } else {
333 if (disp->func->sor.magic)
334 disp->func->sor.magic(outp);
335 }
336
337 exec_clkcmp(disp, head, 0, pclk, &conf);
338
339 if (outp->info.type == DCB_OUTPUT_ANALOG) {
340 addr = 0x612280 + (ffs(outp->info.or) - 1) * 0x800;
341 data = 0x00000000;
342 } else {
343 addr = 0x612300 + (ffs(outp->info.or) - 1) * 0x800;
344 data = (conf & 0x0100) ? 0x00000101 : 0x00000000;
345 switch (outp->info.type) {
346 case DCB_OUTPUT_TMDS:
347 nvkm_mask(device, addr, 0x007c0000, 0x00280000);
348 break;
349 case DCB_OUTPUT_DP:
350 gf119_disp_intr_unk2_2_tu(disp, head, &outp->info);
351 break;
352 default:
353 break;
354 }
355 }
356
357 nvkm_mask(device, addr, 0x00000707, data);
358}

360static void
361gf119_disp_intr_unk4_0(struct nv50_disp *disp, int head)
362{
363 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
364 u32 pclk = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x660450 + (head * 0x300)) / 1000;
365 u32 conf;
366
367 exec_clkcmp(disp, head, 1, pclk, &conf);
368}

370void
371gf119_disp_intr_supervisor(struct work_struct *work)
372{
373 struct nv50_disp *disp =
374 container_of(work, struct nv50_disp, supervisor);
375 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
376 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
377 u32 mask[4];
378 int head;
379
380 nvkm_debug(subdev, "supervisor %d\n", ffs(disp->super));
381 for (head = 0; head < disp->base.head.nr; head++) {
382 mask[head] = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x6101d4 + (head * 0x800));
383 nvkm_debug(subdev, "head %d: %08x\n", head, mask[head]);
384 }
385
386 if (disp->super & 0x00000001) {
387 nv50_disp_chan_mthd(disp->chan[0], NV_DBG_DEBUG);
388 for (head = 0; head < disp->base.head.nr; head++) {
389 if (!(mask[head] & 0x00001000))
390 continue;
391 nvkm_debug(subdev, "supervisor 1.0 - head %d\n", head);
392 gf119_disp_intr_unk1_0(disp, head);
393 }
394 } else
395 if (disp->super & 0x00000002) {
396 for (head = 0; head < disp->base.head.nr; head++) {
397 if (!(mask[head] & 0x00001000))
398 continue;
399 nvkm_debug(subdev, "supervisor 2.0 - head %d\n", head);
400 gf119_disp_intr_unk2_0(disp, head);
401 }
402 for (head = 0; head < disp->base.head.nr; head++) {
403 if (!(mask[head] & 0x00010000))
404 continue;
405 nvkm_debug(subdev, "supervisor 2.1 - head %d\n", head);
406 gf119_disp_intr_unk2_1(disp, head);
407 }
408 for (head = 0; head < disp->base.head.nr; head++) {
409 if (!(mask[head] & 0x00001000))
410 continue;
411 nvkm_debug(subdev, "supervisor 2.2 - head %d\n", head);
412 gf119_disp_intr_unk2_2(disp, head);
413 }
414 } else
415 if (disp->super & 0x00000004) {
416 for (head = 0; head < disp->base.head.nr; head++) {
417 if (!(mask[head] & 0x00001000))
418 continue;
419 nvkm_debug(subdev, "supervisor 3.0 - head %d\n", head);
420 gf119_disp_intr_unk4_0(disp, head);
421 }
422 }
423
424 for (head = 0; head < disp->base.head.nr; head++)
425 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6101d4 + (head * 0x800), 0x00000000);
426 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6101d0, 0x80000000);
427}

429static void
430gf119_disp_intr_error(struct nv50_disp *disp, int chid)
431{
432 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
433 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
434 u32 mthd = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x6101f0 + (chid * 12));
435 u32 data = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x6101f4 + (chid * 12));
436 u32 unkn = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x6101f8 + (chid * 12));
437
438 nvkm_error(subdev, "chid %d mthd %04x data %08x %08x %08x\n",
439 chid, (mthd & 0x0000ffc), data, mthd, unkn);
440
441 if (chid < ARRAY_SIZE(disp->chan)) {
442 switch (mthd & 0xffc) {
443 case 0x0080:
444 nv50_disp_chan_mthd(disp->chan[chid], NV_DBG_ERROR);
445 break;
446 default:
447 break;
448 }
449 }
450
451 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61009c, (1 << chid));
452 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6101f0 + (chid * 12), 0x90000000);
453}
454
455void
456gf119_disp_intr(struct nv50_disp *disp)
457{
458 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
459 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
460 u32 intr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610088);
461 int i;
462
463 if (intr & 0x00000001) {
464 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61008c);
465 while (stat) {
466 int chid = __ffs(stat); stat &= ~(1 << chid);
467 nv50_disp_chan_uevent_send(disp, chid);
468 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61008c, 1 << chid);
469 }
470 intr &= ~0x00000001;
471 }
472
473 if (intr & 0x00000002) {
474 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61009c);
475 int chid = ffs(stat) - 1;
476 if (chid >= 0)
477 gf119_disp_intr_error(disp, chid);
478 intr &= ~0x00000002;
479 }
480
481 if (intr & 0x00100000) {
482 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x6100ac);
483 if (stat & 0x00000007) {
484 disp->super = (stat & 0x00000007);
485 schedule_work(&disp->supervisor);
486 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6100ac, disp->super);
487 stat &= ~0x00000007;
488 }
489
490 if (stat) {
491 nvkm_warn(subdev, "intr24 %08x\n", stat);
492 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6100ac, stat);
493 }
494
495 intr &= ~0x00100000;
496 }
497
498 for (i = 0; i < disp->base.head.nr; i++) {
499 u32 mask = 0x01000000 << i;
500 if (mask & intr) {
501 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x6100bc + (i * 0x800));
502 if (stat & 0x00000001)
503 nvkm_disp_vblank(&disp->base, i);
504 nvkm_mask(device, 0x6100bc + (i * 0x800), 0, 0);
505 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x6100c0 + (i * 0x800));
506 }
507 }
508}

510int
511gf119_disp_new_(const struct nv50_disp_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
512 int index, struct nvkm_disp **pdisp)
513{
514 u32 heads = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x022448);
515 return nv50_disp_new_(func, device, index, heads, pdisp);
516}

518static const struct nv50_disp_func
519gf119_disp = {
520 .intr = gf119_disp_intr,
521 .uevent = &gf119_disp_chan_uevent,
522 .super = gf119_disp_intr_supervisor,
523 .root = &gf119_disp_root_oclass,
524 .head.vblank_init = gf119_disp_vblank_init,
525 .head.vblank_fini = gf119_disp_vblank_fini,
526 .head.scanoutpos = gf119_disp_root_scanoutpos,
527 .outp.internal.crt = nv50_dac_output_new,
528 .outp.internal.tmds = nv50_sor_output_new,
529 .outp.internal.lvds = nv50_sor_output_new,
530 .outp.internal.dp = gf119_sor_dp_new,
531 .dac.nr = 3,
532 .dac.power = nv50_dac_power,
533 .dac.sense = nv50_dac_sense,
534 .sor.nr = 4,
535 .sor.power = nv50_sor_power,
536 .sor.hda_eld = gf119_hda_eld,
537 .sor.hdmi = gf119_hdmi_ctrl,
538};

540int
541gf119_disp_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_disp **pdisp)
542{
543 return gf119_disp_new_(&gf119_disp, device, index, pdisp);
544}
